race.description: Bunbury Forum Fashions On The Field Maiden
race.comment: DESERT WAVES (1) resumed improved with a narrow defeat over this trip at Pinjarra Scarpside. He will position forward again from the inside barrier and has a key jockey switch to Pike. Fitter and can improve again and go one better. DARK OPAL (9) peaks and is a threat, building on her narrow defeat at the track. Gave her all late and will appreciate the longer sprint. CJP is reunited. CAN'T CATCH ME (10) was backed into the red in the DESERT WAVES race and likely had an excuse. Led and missed a whisker at the same track prior and will be fitter again. Will ride the speed from the rails gate and deserves another chance. MAYTHISBETHEONE (11) is heading in the right direction and third-up went close here over 1000m as favourite. Spelled off Stakes grade and the one prior was beaten just 1L in an Open 2 at Ascot on debut. Keep safe.
